Tesla Inc.'s TSLA, +4.50% stock rally has pushed the Silicon Valley car maker's enterprise value to $173.7 billion, with Tesla becoming the No. 1 U.S. car maker by that metric. It surpassed Ford Motor Co.'s F, +0.43% enterprise value for the first time on Tuesday. Enterprise value calculations include a company's market valuation as well as its debt and cash and equivalents and is based on diluted shares. The metric is considered a more complete snapshot of the value of a company. Tesla passed General Motors Co. GM, -0.37% enterprise value for the first time on Jan. 31. Tesla shares have extended their rally and are poised for a closing record, having traded as high as $940.13 on Tuesday, an intraday record. 